{"name":"Berserker (Syn)","type":"ability","img":"icons/weapons/fist/fist-knuckles-spiked-stone.webp","data":{"bonus":{"defense":0,"accurate":0,"cunning":0,"discreet":0,"persuasive":0,"quick":0,"resolute":0,"strong":0,"vigilant":0,"toughness":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"corruption":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"experience":{"value":0,"cost":0}},"description":"<p>The feared barbarian warriors of Davokar have developed the practice of working themselves into a berserker frenzy before battle. <br /><br />By letting the repressed anger of the heart strengthen its limbs, the character can unleash a fuming rage that, if channeled correctly, might determine which side will emerge victorious from the battle.</p>","reference":"berserkerv2","novice":{"isActive":false,"action":"F","description":"<p>As a Free Action, the character may enter into a murderous frenzy to solely focus on hurting the enemy, dealing 1D6 extra damage when fighting in melee combat. The downside of this frenzy is that the character cannot defend itself properly. The attribute on which <em>Defense</em> is based, is considered to be 5 when calculating <em>Defense</em> .</p>"},"adept":{"isActive":false,"action":"R","description":"<p>When damages &gt;= PT, roll STR to cancel effects.</p>"},"master":{"isActive":false,"action":"F","description":"<p>The character has managed to harness its rage without losing any of its power. The character can utilize this capacity to both deal and ignore extra damage, while still being able to defend itself as normal.</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"6uxUbp04gvJupJst":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.symbaroum.symbaroumabilitiesen.64U7yjlWKDeFCyld"}},"_id":"QQyL7hidv9nOyx5l"}
{"name":"Recovery (Syn)","type":"ability","img":"icons/sundries/survival/bedroll-blue-red.webp","data":{"bonus":{"defense":0,"accurate":0,"cunning":0,"discreet":0,"persuasive":0,"quick":0,"resolute":0,"strong":0,"vigilant":0,"toughness":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"corruption":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"experience":{"value":0,"cost":0}},"description":"<p>Among both Black Cloaks and Mystics, meditative techniques that provide strange bodily capabilities have been developed. The character can use its inner power reserves with an almost magical self-discipline to rejuvenate the energy of its body, even when in the midst of combat.</p>","reference":"recoveryv2","novice":{"isActive":false,"action":"A","description":"<p>The character can regain 2D6 Toughness, once per scene. It can only be used in combat.</p>"},"adept":{"isActive":false,"action":"A","description":"<p>Just as novice level, but the character recovers 2D8 Toughness.</p>"},"master":{"isActive":false,"action":"F","description":"<p>Just as adept level, but it is now Free .</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"6uxUbp04gvJupJst":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.symbaroum.symbaroumabilitiesen.9So0gg2IWAk7b4VQ"}},"_id":"Hqf4fVxfTTZCGN9w"}
{"name":"Prios Burning Glass (Syn)","type":"mysticalPower","img":"systems/symbaroum/asset/image/powers/priosburningglass.svg","data":{"bonus":{"defense":0,"accurate":0,"cunning":0,"discreet":0,"persuasive":0,"quick":0,"resolute":0,"strong":0,"vigilant":0,"toughness":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"corruption":{"max":0,"threshold":0},"experience":{"value":0,"cost":0}},"material":"A holy symbol.","description":"<p>The mystic can focus the light of its soul into a burning ray, which damages most beings and destroys the unholy.</p>","reference":"priosburningglassv2","novice":{"isActive":false,"action":"A","description":"<p>With a <em>Resolute</em> test the mystic steers the holy light towards a target, dealing 2D4 damage. The damage increases to 2D6 if the target is an abomination or undead.</p>"},"adept":{"isActive":false,"action":"A","description":"<p>With a successful <em>Resolute</em> test, the mystic can let the holy light pass over all enemies in sight. The burning energy deals 2D6 damage, 2D8 on abominations and undead.</p>"},"master":{"isActive":false,"action":"A","description":"<p>With a <em>Resolute</em> test the mystic can let his or her inner light shine over all nearby enemies, dealing 2D6 damage, increased to 2D8 if the enemies are abominations or &shy;undead. The mystic can also stun all thoroughly corrupt and undead enemies for one turn if he or she succeeds with a [<em>Resolute</em>&larr;<em>Resolute</em>] test.</p>"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"iVakC8l8lGvyE0t0":3,"mGLPdRGFwUvDwucD":3,"bekKw2VqJj8hwN65":3,"Q7Rf9xhS1Q55LGct":3,"6uxUbp04gvJupJst":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.symbaroum.symbaroumpowersen.w1MXf2fxwdwd14Lt"}},"_id":"pHgdoDaLJUcavOzp"}